Determines the date and time based on the arguments. The * arguments are interpreted as a year, month, day of the month, * hour of the day, minute within the hour, and second within the * minute, exactly as for the <tt>Date</tt> constructor with six * arguments, except that the arguments are interpreted relative * to UTC rather than to the local time zone. The time indicated is * returned represented as the distance, measured in milliseconds, * of that time from the epoch (00:00:00 GMT on January 1, 1970).
